sentences.english: I grew up in Los Angeles actually, West Wood.
sentences.chinese: 实际上，我是在洛杉矶西木区长大的。

sentences.english: He became a rector of a small parish where he ministered for several years.
sentences.chinese: 他成为一个小教区的教区长，在那里主事了几年圣事。

sentences.english: The rector had gone away for the day, being a man who disliked the sight of changes.
sentences.chinese: 教区长素来不愿意看到变动，所以整天都到外边去了。

sentences.english: They had evidently been paying a visit to the vicar.
sentences.chinese: 他们分明是刚拜访教区长来着。

sentences.english: He was a Democratic precinct captain and worked at the city water filtration plant in Chicago.
sentences.chinese: 他曾是民主党选区区长，在芝加哥市水过滤厂工作。

sentences.english: Changgou Village in Qiqihaar City, China is the stopover site of Hooded Crane.
sentences.chinese: 齐齐哈尔市铁峰区长沟村是白头鹤南北迁徙的停歇地。

sentences.english: The rectory burned but the church itself was spared.
sentences.chinese: 教区长的住宅烧毁，但教堂本身幸免。

sentences.english: Mr. Tang, who was the first head of Mituo District, is a big shot.
sentences.chinese: 弥陀区第一任区长，人称有“宰宰权”的大人物。
